# Code Style and Documentation Guidelines

## Language Standards

- **Comments**: Always write in English for better international collaboration
- **Documentation**: Write in English for technical documentation
- **User-facing text**: Use Traditional Chinese (繁體中文) for responses and user interface
- **Error messages**: Use Traditional Chinese for user-facing errors

## Python Code Style

- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use type hints for all function parameters and return values
- Use descriptive variable and function names in English
- Prefer async/await over callbacks when possible
- Use Pydantic models for data validation

## Documentation Structure

- Place all documentation in [docs/](mdc:docs/) directory
- Use Markdown format for documentation files
- Include code examples in documentation
- Keep README.md updated with current usage patterns

## Example Code

- Place examples in [examples/](mdc:examples/) directory
- Examples should be self-contained and runnable
- Include comprehensive comments explaining the code
- Demonstrate both sync and async usage patterns

## Model Design

- Use Pydantic models for all data structures
- Keep models in [src/pueue_wrapper/models/](mdc:src/pueue_wrapper/models/)
- Provide convenience methods for common operations
- Include proper type annotations and default values
